588
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,199
I went on a picnic and
ate pudding out of a can.

589
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,200
it was horrible.

590
00:33:49,511 --> 00:33:51,199
Well, if it makes you feel any better,

591
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,600
I dragged to the ballet the other night.

592
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,900
So you are dating.

593
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:01,500
That's why you've been
lifting weights and jogging.

594
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:04,300
Well, if you wanna bag the big game,

595
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:06,700
Gotta work on the guns.

596
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:13,400
I'll give you this--

597
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:17,500
you're gon be a tough
act to follow, Carlos.

598
00:34:23,700 --> 00:34:25,000
Back at ya, babe.

599
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:42,999
I'm so sorry to keep you waiting,

600
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,360
but I don't want to introduce you

601
00:34:44,361 --> 00:34:47,000
- until all my guests are here.
- I don't mind.

602
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:49,600
By the way, um,

603
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:53,099
when my friends ask you what happened--

604
00:34:53,100 --> 00:34:54,100
and they will--

605
00:34:54,700 --> 00:34:57,200
I don't think it's necessary
to go into all that

606
00:34:57,300 --> 00:35:00,199
unpleasantness about Orson and Monique.

607
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:01,099
All they need to know

608
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:03,900
is that you're back
and we're on good terms.

609
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:06,000
And Orson didn't kill me.

610
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:09,100
And Orson didn't kill you.

611
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,800
Oh, okay, just o minute.
That'll be Susan.

612
00:35:36,900 --> 00:35:39,299
Hi. I brought you a bundt cake.

613
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,699
Don't worry. I didn't make it.

614
00:35:40,700 --> 00:35:43,099
- Oh, you didn't have to do that.
- I was really touched

615
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:45,199
it was so big of you.

616
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:48,100
Well, when you're wrong, You're wrong.

617
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:52,799
Now that we're all assembled,

618
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:55,400
I'd like to introduce
the guest of honor.

619
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:58,518
I hope you'll all be as
delighted to meet her as I was.

620
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:00,700
You can me in now.

621
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:08,200
Everyone, this is Alma Hodge.

622
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:10,000
Orson's first wife.

623
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:16,600
Oh, about that apology...

624
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,100
Any time you're ready.

625
00:36:21,100 --> 00:36:23,800
So you have been in canada
this entire time?

626
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,399
Well, my aunt Agnes has
a place in Winnipeg.

627
00:36:26,548 --> 00:36:28,299
I hadn't planned on staying slong,

628
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:30,423
but I needed the time to find myself.

629
00:36:30,697 --> 00:36:32,651
It would've been nice if
someone to found you.

630
00:36:32,856 --> 00:36:34,689
There was a whole lot
of drama around here.

631
00:36:34,690 --> 00:36:35,699
Yes, I heard.

632
00:36:35,700 --> 00:36:38,500
People actually thought
Orson had done away with me?

633
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,099
Amazing, isn't it,

634
00:36:41,100 --> 00:36:43,100
Where some people's minds will go?

635
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:49,399
- Well, you gotta hand it to her.
- Just when you think

636
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:51,299
Bree's thrown every
conceivable theme party,

637
00:36:51,300 --> 00:36:52,599
she hosts a "shame on you

638
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:54,630
for thinking my husband
killed someone" dinner.

639
00:36:54,904 --> 00:36:56,672
So Alma's alive. big deal.

640
00:36:56,673 --> 00:36:59,299
We still don't know what went
down between Orson and Monique.

641
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:02,199
Susan, please. we look stupid
enough for suspecting him.

642
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:03,300
Just let it go.

643
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,500
It may be a little late for that.

644
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:12,999
Detective Ridley. Can I help you?

645
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,200
Yes. I'd like to speak to your husband.

646
00:37:16,700 --> 00:37:18,299
Oh, well, I'm afraid he's not here,

647
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:21,200
but I will be happy to tell him
that you came by.

648
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:22,700
<i>Who is it, darling?</i>

649
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,100
Excuse us.

650
00:37:31,100 --> 00:37:33,600
Can't this wait?
We're having a dinner party.

651
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:36,500
Hello, Dr. Hodge.

652
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,000
Detective Ridley.

653
00:37:38,100 --> 00:37:40,299
We need you to come with us.
We have some questions

654
00:37:40,300 --> 00:37:42,851
about that Jane Doe we
showed you in the morgue.

655
00:37:42,988 --> 00:37:45,599
Why do you think I'd know
anything about her?

656
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:48,700
Well, you were having an affair
with her when she died.

657
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,300
Oh, where did you hear that?

658
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:58,400
Susan?

659
00:38:00,100 --> 00:38:02,300
I didn't know they were
gonna come tonight.

660
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:06,999
Uh, I'm happy to answer any questions

661
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:08,299
that you might have.

662
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:11,400
My apologies. Please, stay.
Enjoy the dessert.

663
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:17,399
I don't believe this.

664
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:19,099
You called the police?

665
00:38:19,100 --> 00:38:20,999
Well, obviously, you weren't going to.

666
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,999
They needed to know that that
dead woman was Orson's mistress.

667
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,999
- I told you that in confidence.
- Did you seriously think

668
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:30,300
I could sit on information
that would exonerate Mike?

669
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:33,300
If you had seen his face
in jail the other day...

670
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:35,700
The other day?
You-- you saw Mike?

671
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:39,200
Yeah. I-- just to tell him
about the lawyer.

672
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,899
I know that Mike is innocent.

673
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:44,200
Right, just like you knew she was dead.

674
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,300
I thought we had an agreement.

675
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,999
We do. Can we talk about this later?

676
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:50,800
When?

677
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:53,400
After your next conjugal visit?

678
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:55,800
Ian. wait!

679
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:58,900
Boy, when it comes to Mike,
there's no one you won't betray.

680
00:38:59,300 --> 00:39:00,400
excuse me?

681
00:39:01,100 --> 00:39:02,199
Hey, guys...

682
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:03,599
Please leave my house.

683
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:05,900
Bree! You heard me. Get out!

684
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:07,728
Okay, Bree, I know you're angry,

685
00:39:07,729 --> 00:39:09,199
but for the sake of our friendship--

686
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:12,900
Oh, make no mistake,
our friendship is over.

687
00:39:19,300 --> 00:39:21,299
Okay. you go...

688
00:39:21,300 --> 00:39:22,300
Okay.

689
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:30,600
So, Winnipeg...

690
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:34,000
must get pretty cold up there.

691
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:39,752
I'm just getting my coat.

692
00:39:39,753 --> 00:39:41,999
Ian, please, I just lost
one of my best friends.

693
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,159
I can't lose you, too.

694
00:39:43,237 --> 00:39:45,199
You said that you wouldn't
see him again.

695
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:47,599
but you had to know that
I would go one more time

696
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:50,099
- to just explain everything.
- Actually, no, I didn't.

697
00:39:50,100 --> 00:39:52,000
Well, that's just crazy!

698
00:39:52,100 --> 00:39:53,999
Why are you acting like a crazy person?

699
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:56,700
Because you've already
left me once for this--this guy!

700
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:59,299
Things are different now!
I love you!

701
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:01,600
You don't have to worry
about that anymore.

702
00:40:02,143 --> 00:40:03,960
If we're gonna make
this relationship work,

703
00:40:03,961 --> 00:40:07,600
then you have to trust me,
and why are you smiling at me?

704
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:10,600
- You just said that you love me.
- Yeah? So?

705
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,499
- Well, you've never said that before.
- Yes, I have.

706
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:15,299
No. I would've remembered.

707
00:40:15,300 --> 00:40:17,099
well, I'm saying it now.
I love you.

708
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:19,699
- Do you have a problem with that?
- No, ma'am.

709
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:22,099
you--you--you can't kiss me now.
I'm yelling at you.

710
00:40:22,100 --> 00:40:23,099
Well, I'm listening.

711
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:25,499
well... don't think that you can

712
00:40:25,500 --> 00:40:27,400
get out of this, you know, by just...

713
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:31,899
Oh, god. oh, yeah, uh,
oh, yeah, right--right there.

714
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:32,908
Oh, right there.

715
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:39,600
Look, I think we should stop doing this.

716
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:42,899
I know it's my idea,

717
00:40:42,900 --> 00:40:45,800
but it just doesn't feel right anymore.

718
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:50,000
You slept with Julie. It's no big deal.

719
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:51,655
Well, it is to her,

720
00:40:51,811 --> 00:40:53,399
And I don't want
to see her get hurt.

721
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,800
Me, either.

722
00:40:56,300 --> 00:40:57,900
So let's just not tell her.

723
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,500
<i>There's no place in fairview
that's more peaceful.</i>

724
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:09,700
All the floorsre hardwood.

725
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:11,900
Oh, there are brand-new appliances.

726
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,300
And the gardens are...

727
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:15,000
well, they're beautiful.

728
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:18,600
So... what do you think?

729
00:41:21,300 --> 00:41:22,400
I'll take it.

730
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,799
Really? That's terrific!

731
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:27,700
I'll draw up the papers in the morning.

732
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,500
if you don't mind me asking,

733
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:37,800
Why were you so interested
in this particular street?

734
00:41:38,100 --> 00:41:41,100
I've been moving around a lot
in the last few months,

735
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:44,099
and I need a place where
I can really settle down.

736
00:41:44,100 --> 00:41:45,300
you know what I mean?

737
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:50,085
<i>I wanna live in a place where
children know how to behave,</i>

738
00:41:50,100 --> 00:41:53,899
<i>where people still have
some sense of moral value,</i>

739
00:41:53,900 --> 00:41:57,199
<i>and where friendships are good.</i>

740
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,900
<i>and strong and last forever.</i>

741
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,100
That is what I looking for

742
00:42:04,258 --> 00:42:07,400
Then I think Wisteria Lane
is the place for you.

743
00:42:08,700 --> 00:42:09,400
good.

744
00:42:10,100 --> 00:42:12,300
more than anything,
I just wanna fit in.

745
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:17,099
Oh, you will, Alma.

746
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:19,400
<i>You absolutely will.</i>

